# Tailwind canonical classes

Follow `tailwindcss(suggestCanonicalClasses)`. Use Tailwind’s canonical utility names (especially v4 renames) instead of legacy aliases in `className` strings and CSS `@apply`.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<div className="bg-gradient-to-r from-white to-transparent" />

// ✅ GOOD
<div className="bg-linear-to-r from-white to-transparent" />
```

When the Tailwind language server or linter suggests a canonical replacement, apply it. Do not introduce or leave deprecated aliases in edited files.

Keep intentional exceptions:
- Arbitrary radii that do not match theme `--radius-*` tokens (e.g. `rounded-[4px]`)
- Dynamic CSS-variable utilities such as `border-(--color-border)` (not theme `border`)
